&quot;Nephew, when one God is killed in the other Universe, the other shall die in our world. For some reason, Alysia has prevented that. Our blessings go to her and her marriage to the Devi.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uzeuskingofthegods.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeus King of the Gods</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/17/01 10:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stepping in. .. </span><hr size=1> Zeus' eyes raged with lightning.  He pointed an accusing finger at Alysia.  &quot;This is no goddess.  She is not of Olympian blood.  She cares not about worshiping us as is proper. She wants only your blessings with nothing in return.  On Olympus, there is no such thing.  You give nothing, you get nothing.&quot;<br>
<br>
He continued his dissertation, &quot;By her own words she states..'I do not need the blessings of Olympian Gods because of the ways that we follow. I myself am a Goddess of such order by your rites, and in equality of eachother, I ask a blessing from you on my marriage to the Avatar.'  Be it known from this day forward, that no other false gods are equal to Olympians nor will they be blessed by Olympians.  Our blessings are to be given ONLY to those who live in accordance with Olympian law.&quot;<br>
<br>
His raging eyes then turn to Poseidon, &quot;Dear Brother or shall I now refer to you as Dear Sister, she asked not for your blessing, yet you offer it as if it is a prized gift to this individual.&quot;  He laughs heartily, &quot;And again I will give you her exact words. 'Because of my ties to the amazons, I ask for your blessings as well dear Goddess Sisters.'  Again let me reiterate, the Olympians are NOT your sisters.&quot;<br>
<br>
Again he faced Poseidon, &quot;Cling to your trident dear sister,&quot; his voice booming with sarcasm, &quot;I am the god of justice.  It is written that I am a fair god and a just god.  So therefore, yes, my ways are just and right.&quot;<br>
<br>
Zeus then glares at Alysia, &quot;You are not welcome here as the other gods and goddesses, you hold no title bestowed upon you by any Olympian; therefore, it is of little consequence to us.&quot;<br>
<br>
The furies turn came soon enough.  &quot;Do not speak to me of such lies.  Do not speak of things not written.&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/17/01 8:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> She laughed. . .</span><hr size=1> She smirked lightly as she folded her arms looking at the God. She then passed him lightly and looked to the others in respect. &quot;I thank you all for your kind workds to me. In due time, I shall show my gratitude.&quot;<br>
